": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8434362, "raw_content": "The President can impose tariffs via other laws, such as:\n\n- Section 232 (Trade Expansion Act 1962) for national security threats.\n- Section 301 (Trade Act 1974) for unfair trade practices.\n- Section 201 (Trade Act 1974) against import surges.\n- Section 122 (Trade Act 1974) for balance-of-payments issues.\n\nThe SCOTUS ruling only restricts IEEPA.\n\nDon't get upset by all the master rage baiters.\n", "author": "Herpawinski", "created": 1771603893848, "profile_picture": "GCJCeufYDd47", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Tiger5468", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Calm down. The Scotus ruling only applies their implementation via IEEPA. There are multiple other avenues to enact tariffs.", "last_comment_created": 1771637325894, "content": "<p>The President can impose tariffs via other laws, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Section 232 (Trade Expansion Act 1962) for national security threats.</li>\n<li>Section 301 (Trade Act 1974) for unfair trade practices.</li>\n<li>Section 201 (Trade Act 1974) against import surges.</li>\n<li>Section 122 (Trade Act 1974) for balance-of-payments issues.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The SCOTUS ruling only restricts IEEPA.</p>\n<p>Don't get upset by all the master rage baiters.</p>\n", "score_down": 2, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 8, "score_up": 240, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASFqqz4V8", "is_twi